kelly_bot_ml.py  —  Kelly Criterion Bot v3
==========================================
Probability engine: XGBoost + calibration comparison
  (Isotonic | Platt/Sigmoid | Beta — best is auto-selected by Brier score)

Features:
  - Price returns   : 1, 3, 6, 12, 24, 48-bar log returns
  - RSI / Momentum  : RSI-14, RSI-6, rate-of-change, MACD signal
  - Volatility      : rolling std (6,24,48-bar), ATR-14, realised vol ratio
  - Volume          : volume z-score, OBV slope, buy/sell volume imbalance

Validation:
  - Anchored walk-forward (n folds)
  - Calibration curve comparison across all three methods
  - Brier score, log-loss, ROC-AUC per fold
  - Feature importance plot
  - Wilson CI lower-bound used as conservative p in Kelly

Usage examples:
  python kelly_bot_ml.py --symbol BTCUSDT --interval 1h --mode backtest
  python kelly_bot_ml.py --symbol BTCUSDT --interval 1h --mode validate
  python kelly_bot_ml.py --symbol SOLUSDT --interval 4h --mode backtest --gain 0.04 --loss 0.02
"""

